==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cleistocarp
<hw>cleistocarp</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the closed spore-bearing
structure of some fungi (especially <fam>Aspergillaceae</fam> and
<fam>Eurysiphaceae</fam>) from which spores are released only by decay
or disintegration; -- called also
<altname>cleistothecium</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cleistothecium.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cleistogamous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Cleistogamic</ent>⟦br⟧
